{
  "stem": "812.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 104,
      "text": "It may not always have been exactly the size or the shape as the first two or three.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 105,
      "text": "But I rationalized, and I felt that this is the best I could do here.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 106,
      "text": "It'll be fine.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 107,
      "text": "We will all survive.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 108,
      "text": "I have my four pebbles.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 109,
      "text": "And it gave me the little extra strength and extra hope.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 110,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] We, as I said, we went through some bitter cold days, and it was not unusual to-- to have frostbites.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 111,
      "text": "And of course, there was nothing that-- we had nothing to care for, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] no medication, no nothing to care for our frostbitten fingers or toes.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 112,
      "text": "And we used to treat them with the warmth of our own urine.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 113,
      "text": "That's all that we had to soothe the discomfort with.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 114,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Once a week, we were sent out-- taken to an area to shower.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 115,
      "text": "We had heard of extermination camps.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 116,
      "text": "We had heard of Auschwitz, and we knew of the gas chambers there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 117,
      "text": "And we were told that we were just to go to the showers and there, under the watchful eyes of the Germans, we were told to undress, and we were sent into the showers.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 118,
      "text": "And of course, we never knew when those faucets were turned on whether it would be gas that would come out or water.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 119,
      "text": "So there, again, the Germans did everything in their power to ridiculous us, to torment us, and it was just another way.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 120,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 9 SECONDS] It was impossible to keep oneself clean.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 121,
      "text": "We were covered with lice-- hair lice, clothes lice.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 122,
      "text": "There we learned that there was a distinct difference between hair lice and clothes lice.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
